I'm thrilled to share my second HTML project, built as part of the REVOU Full Stack Software Engineer Program! In this assignment, I focused on crafting a solid website structure using fundamental HTML, adhering to the program's guidelines.

Through this project, I explored about building a scematic HTML code. I encountered certain challenges related to make this code can clearly understandable by other people, but I successfully navigated them by using the scematic HTML method that hopefully can be understandable and more structurize. ## How to run this code

### 1. Requirement

To see this website page you can run it with your browser app like [google chrome]() (recommended)

### 2. Clone The Repository

Open this [repository in github](https://github.com/RevoU-FSSE-4/module-1-AlvaroSeptra.git) in your terminal by typing

```bash
git clone https://github.com/RevoU-FSSE
```

Use the following command in your terminal/command prompt to clone the repository onto your local machine.

## How to edit this code (Recommended steps)

### 1. Basic Recommended Requirement

To run the website, you will need:

- NodeJS installed on your computer (version 8 or above)
- A text editor/IDE (such as Visual Studio Code)

### 2. Clone The Repository

Open this [repository in github](https://github.com/RevoU-FSSE-4/module-1-AlvaroSeptra.git) in your terminal by typing

```bash
git clone https://github.com/RevoU-FSSE
```

Use the following command in your terminal/command prompt to clone the repository onto your local machine.

### 3. Open file and run

Open the folder where you have saved the downloaded repository then open `about.html` file in your preferred text editor. Then simply press Ctrl + F5 or use the "Go Live" button from VSCode "index.html" from VSCode
